# Component Rules

## Component Structure
Follow this structure for all components:

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  // Imports
  // Props interface
  // Local state
  // Functions
</script>

<!-- Template -->
<template>
  <!-- Component markup -->
</template>

<style>
  /* Scoped or global styles */
</style>
```

## Props and Events
- Define props with TypeScript interfaces
- Use Svelte's prop validation
- Emit typed events
- Document props with JSDoc

## Accessibility
- Add ARIA labels to all interactive elements
- Support keyboard navigation
- Manage focus appropriately
- Announce errors to screen readers
- Use semantic HTML

## Styling
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Follow responsive design patterns
- Support mobile, tablet, and desktop
- Use Foundation Health branding colors
- Implement focus states for accessibility

## Component-Specific Rules

### Input Components
- Validate input in real-time
- Show error messages clearly
- Provide helper text and examples
- Support autocomplete where appropriate
- Handle loading states

### Display Components
- Show loading states
- Handle empty states
- Display errors gracefully
- Support keyboard navigation
- Make data copyable when appropriate

### Results Components
- Highlight important information
- Show warnings prominently
- Make tables sortable
- Support responsive layouts
- Provide JSON export

## Performance
- Use Svelte's reactivity efficiently
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Lazy load heavy components
- Debounce user inputs
- Optimize list rendering
